com.satori.rtm.connection

Class Connection

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.satori.rtm.connection.Connection

  • public class Connection
extends java.lang.Object
    Access RTM at the connection level to connect, send and receive PDUs, and wait for responses.

    Create a Connection with the create() method.

    Code Example 

     
 Connection connection = Connection.create(new URI("<ENDPOINT>?appkey=<APP_KEY>"),
                                           new WebSocketTransportFactory());
 connection.connect(new ConnectionListener() { ... });

        public com.google.common.util.concurrent.ListenableFuture<java.lang.Void> sendNoAck(java.lang.String operation,

        Asynchronously sends a Protocol Data Unit (PDU) to RTM without acknowledgement

        This method creates a PDU from an operation and an object. It then sends the PDU to RTM. The object must be serializable into a JSON object.

      • send

        public <T> com.google.common.util.concurrent.ListenableFuture<Pdu<T>> send(java.lang.String operation,
                                                                           java.lang.Object body,
                                                                           java.lang.Class<T> responseClazz)
        Asynchronously sends a Protocol Data Unit (PDU) to RTM.

        This method creates a PDU from an operation and an object. It then sends the PDU to RTM. The object must be serializable into a JSON object.

        Use responseClazz to specify the format of the PDU body returned by RTM. The body is converted to an object of type responseClazz before it's returned.

        This method returns a ListenableFuture that completes when a response is received from RTM.

        The ListenableFuture can fail due to the following error:

        • PduException: an RTM error occured.
        Type Parameters:
        T - the response object type
        Parameters:
        operation - PDU operation, for example, "rtm/publish"
        body - PDU body
        responseClazz - a Class instance of the response object type
        Returns:
        result of the send operation

      • sendWithCallback

        public <T> void sendWithCallback(java.lang.String operation,
                                 java.lang.Object body,
                                 java.lang.Class<T> responseClazz,
                                 Callback<Pdu<T>> callback)
        Asynchronously sends a Protocol Data Unit (PDU) to RTM. The response from RTM is passed to the callback.

        This method creates a PDU from an operation and an object. It then sends the PDU to RTM. The object must be serializable into a JSON object.

        Use responseClazz to specify the format of the PDU body returned by RTM. The body is converted to an object of type responseClazz before it's returned.

        Use this method when RTM responds with multiple PDUs. All of the response PDUs are passed to callback.onResponse().

        Type Parameters:
        T - the response object type
        Parameters:
        operation - PDU operation, for example, "rtm/publish"
        body - PDU body
        responseClazz - a Class instance of the response object type
        callback - callback that RTM invokes with the response or responses

      • dispose

        public void dispose()
        Stops a specific connection and releases all allocated resources. All communication with RTM stops when you call this method and the events aren't propagated to any listeners.

        In general, use this method after the connection to RTM is already closed and you need to clean up resources.

      • close

        public void close()
        Closes a specific connection. The TransportListener.onDisconnected() event is propagated to all listeners.
